abstract: Ms. Plame is celebrating her C.I.A. past in a race for a congressional seat. But as she finds herself cast as an outsider, she’s running into trouble.
snippet: Ms. Plame is celebrating her C.I.A. past in a race for a congressional seat. But as she finds herself cast as an outsider, she’s running into trouble.
lead_paragraph: SANTA FE, N.M. — When Valerie Plame declared her run for Congress by boasting of her past as a C.I.A. agent, money poured into her campaign from donors around the country charmed by her vow to take on President Trump.

abstract: Receiving a “political benefit” does not transform an otherwise legal action (like requesting an investigation) into an abuse of power.
snippet: Receiving a “political benefit” does not transform an otherwise legal action (like requesting an investigation) into an abuse of power.
lead_paragraph: The way things look, President Trump will almost certainly not be removed from office. The precedents set by the articles of impeachment, however, will endure far longer. And regrettably, the House of Representatives has transformed presidential impeachment from a constitutional parachute — an emergency measure to save the Republic in free-fall — into a parliamentary vote of “no confidence.”

abstract: The socialist from Vermont is not a threat to American democracy. The president is.
snippet: The socialist from Vermont is not a threat to American democracy. The president is.
lead_paragraph: Bernie Sanders is surging. What has changed? It cannot be the candidate, because, rightly or wrongly, voters perceive Mr. Sanders as always being his same sincere, authentic self. One thought is that, given how the Democratic field has narrowed, he might in the end be the man to beat President Trump, since he appeals to many of the angry citizens who proved decisive in 2016 — an anti-establishment message vigorously pushed by the Sanders campaign itself.

abstract: World leaders converged in Jerusalem to mark the 75th anniversary of the liberation of Auschwitz.
snippet: World leaders converged in Jerusalem to mark the 75th anniversary of the liberation of Auschwitz.
lead_paragraph: This briefing has ended. Read about how some of the world leaders gathered in Jerusalem invoked the past to score present-day political points.
